</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-620">where "r" is the linear distance of the particle from the point of contact. We must know that angular velocity vector and position vector are perpendicular to each other. As such, the "sinθ" term in the magnitude of a vector product always evaluates to "1".</para><para id="element-55">
<term> 6.</term> The velocity is tangential to the circular path i.e. perpendicular to position vector.
</para>
